main event: An unidentified flying object was reported to have landed on the sand in the Gulf of Mexico, hovered just under the clouds, and was observed both visually and by ground radar.
interesting points: The object was about 30 feet in diameter, dark in color, and moved slowly and silently,The sighting lasted for about 30 minutes,Observers were dispatched by the USAF after a deputy sheriff reported a bright light that seemed abnormal,Another observation indicated a glowing light that disappeared after about 2 hours,The conclusions of the event noted it took place but then denied that it occurred.
witness description: the observer was a Tampa/Hillsborough County Deputy Sheriff
